<TITLE> 7 killed in 2 highway accidents in Chouddagram </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, Oct 9 (bdnews24.com)  A passenger bus and a microbus collided head-on on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Chouddagram Tuesday morning, leaving six killed and eight injured, police said. Chouddagram police chief Mostafizur Rahman said in another accident, a Dhaka-bound truck ran over an unidentified youth in his teens at Batisha Bazaar at around 9:30am, killing him on the spot. He said a Comilla-Feni passenger bus hit a passenger-ridden microbus travelling from Cox's Bazaar to Dhaka at Bashantapur on the highway at 5 am. Two on board the microbus died on the spot, two others died from their wounds at Chouddagram Upazila Health Complex and another two succumbed to injuries at Comilla Medical College Hospital, Rahman said. The dead were identified as microbus driver Sirajul Islam, Moulana Matiur Rahman, Hafez Mahbubur Rahman, Anwar Hossain, Syed Ismail and Abdus Samad. The police chief said the deceased were all from Mirpur, Dhaka. The injured Delwar Hossain, Masudur Rahman, Abdul Mannan, Shamshuddoha and Zakir Hossain from Mirpur, Ataur Rahman from Chuadanga, Rabiul Alam from Rajshahi and Mozammel Hossain from Tongi had been sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital for treatment, Rahman said. Police seized the errant bus, but its driver managed to flee. bdnews24.c
